## Phase 6 — Permission Gate Implementation

The `PermissionGate` component checks `authStore.tier`:
- `free` → renders blurred children + "Upgrade to Student/Pro" overlay
- `student` → renders children (some gated features still blur for Pro-only)
- `professional` → renders all children

**Locked features by tier:**

| Feature | Free | Student | Pro |
|---|---|---|---|
| Job feed top 3 | ✓ | Top 10 | Top 25 |
| Fit reasons / skill gaps | Blurred | ✓ | ✓ |
| Auto-apply | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| Daily coach (WhatsApp) | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |
| LinkedIn networking | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| Follow-up reminders | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `PermissionGate` must NEVER hide locked features — it must always **blur + show upgrade CTA**. This is per `system.md` ui_qa rule: "locked feature hidden not blurred → BLOCKED".

